The best way to keep up with our team is through modelun.fiu.edu or through our Instagram(@FIUModelUN). Applications for the spring semester will be closed a week before the last day to add/drop August 21th

Name: FIU Online
Description: With over 20 years’ experience in online education, FIU Online provides you with the opportunity to earn more than a degree. It’s your future.

Name: FIU Peer Mentor Program
Description:
The Peer Mentor program is for students who want to be FIU student leaders by assisting First Year Experience instructors throughout the length of the course. Peer Mentors guide fellow peers (approx. 20) throughout their first semester of college and are a great resource for students in and outside of the classroom. Peer Mentors have the opportunity to lead group activities and discussions during the class and establish special bonds with the students and instructor.

Peer Mentor Applications are now open until February 9th, 2024.

Name: FIU Psychedelic Club
Description:
The FIU Psychedelic Club invites students to discuss the evolving research about psychedelics in the medical and psychotherapy fields, the potential of psychedelics as alternative therapies, and the psychedelic renaissance. 

We are always accepting new members, regardless of major or academic interests!

We do not endorse psychedelic use

Name: FIU Psychology
Description: Through teaching, engagement and cutting-edge discoveries, we're preparing the next generation of researchers and educators. With strong curricula and research, we've gained national prominence for our outstanding faculty and programs. We are committed to actively promoting diversity, equity and inclusion as a professional and moral imperative at the individual, group and system levels as we honor the APA code of ethics, particularly the principles of “justice” and “respect for people’s rights and dignity,” and embrace FIU’s commitment to fostering a climate of inclusion within a diverse community.

Name: FIU Student Media
Description: The Department of Student Media combines PantherNOW, a newspaper produced by FIU students, and The Roar, a student-run radio station. PantherNOW is published Wednesdays during the regular academic year and content is posted daily on PantherNOW.com. The Roar runs 24 hours, seven days a week.

Name: Florida Engineering Society
Description:
Florida Engineering Society @FIU is the Source for Quality STEM and Technical Talent. The goal of the Florida Engineering Society is to mold our members into valuable and powerful assets sought after by our industry. As our name implies, this club will connect you to fellow engineers throughout the state and contribute to your development as a professional engineer. In the past, our members have made continued impactful contributions within and outside of the engineering field as managers, consultants, and officers in the armed forces.

The objectives of the Chapter are to promote and enhance the education, knowledge, welfare, ethical standards, and best interests of the engineering profession and the individuals engaged in the engineering profession for the benefit of the profession and the general public

Name: Florida International Student Institute for Computational Applications
Description: N/A

Name: Formula SAE
Description: We strive to gain and maintain worldwide recognition from the automotive industry, as well as respect from our fellow engineering students, faculty, and sponsors. Additionally, we intend to develop our program for future generations who want to learn how to build a racecar, work in a team, and take on the challenge of balancing club involvement with academic workload.

Name: Friends of MSF at FIU
Description: As a nationally affiliated student chapter of the Doctors Without Borders non-profit organization, we aim to help reduce the burden of global health crises, inequality, and impoverishment both around the world as well as in our local community. We will accomplish our goals by actively fundraising for the Doctors Without Borders organization, engaging in volunteer efforts at FIU and within the local community, hosting prominent guest speakers from FIU, Doctors Without Borders, and other organizations, and more. In addition, the Friends Of MSF chapter at FIU will help students of any major find a path by which they may aid in humanitarian efforts around the world.

Name: Front Office Test
Description: N/A

Name: Frost Art Museum - FIU
Description:
The Patricia & Phillip Frost Art Museum's mission is to provide transformative experiences through art; collect, exhibit, and interpret art across cultures; and advance FIU’s stature as a top tier research university.

One of the largest academic art museums in South Florida, the Patricia & Phillip Frost Art Museum provides the community with free access to world-class art that spans cultures and time periods. The museum started as a small space in FIU’s Primera Casa building in 1978. As the collection and programming grew, the university recognized the need for a dedicated museum space. The museum now resides in a beautiful 46,000 square foot building designed by Yann Weymouth and situated in the heart of FIU’s Avenue of the Arts. The museum opened its doors in 2008.

Name: Future Nurses of America
Description: FNA is a student-led organization dedicated to guiding their members towards their desired goals within the nursing field by offering resources including: community service events, studying tips/resources, information on certification opportunities, nursing school application assistance, as well as direct exposure to professional personnel from the nursing field. These experiences aim to enhance their academic development while simultaneously making them competitive applicants when applying to nursing schools across the nation.

Name: Garden Club
Description: Mission: To provide a space for the FIU community to gain knowledge about the importance of local and sustainably grown food.

Name: GearShifters
Description: The GearShifters is a philanthropic vehicle enthusiast social club. With bi-monthly meets, fundraisers, social events, and volunteering opportunities, with aspire to provide a platform for those with a passion for cars, trucks, motorcycles, and other vehicles to share their passion in a safe manner. We promote the safe operation of all vehicles while allowing for motorsport experiences through drag racing, autocross events, and other insured and sanctioned events. Come join us in shifting the perception of the South Florida car community! Join us in our fight to make our love for cars mean something to each other and to the community! All FIU students are eligible to join, no vehicle is required. I hope to meet you soon, GearShifter.

Name: Geek Culture Club
Description:
The Geek Culture Club is a club where all fandoms are embraced. This club will have panel discussions, costume workshops, video game tournaments, and much much more. The goal of our club is to bring together the like-minded people at FIU to make a happier, geekier world.

 

If you're interested, consider joining our Discord Server!

Name: Geology Club @FIU
Description: We are passionate about our planet and the geologic processes which allow its existence. All are welcome to join us and share our love of this planet! We host multiple social and educational events throughout the year.

Name: GitStart
Description: N/A

Name: Global Brigades @ FIU
Description: N/A

Name: Global Forensic and Justice Center
Description: We coordinate all forensic science and criminal justice efforts at FIU. Our purpose is equitable justice through science, scholarship, and service. Our structure builds on four established focus areas - Academia, Industry, Technology and International Justice - dramatically expanding the university's footprint and providing unparalleled opportunities for students, postdocs, faculty, practitioners and agencies worldwide.

Name: Global Health Interest Group
Description: N/A

Name: Global Learning
Description: N/A

Name: GLOBAL STUDIES STUDENT ASSOCIATION
Description: This organization is an undergraduate student organization that will serve all Global studies majors, minors, and all FIU students who are interested in understanding local and global issues from an anthropological, sociological, geographical, and interdisciplinary perspectives. The organization aims to create a social and an academic community to organize both social and academic events that will create awareness among FIU students on Global issues.

Name: Graduate and Professional Student Committee
Description:
The Graduate & Professional Student Committee (GPSC) helps facilitate and enhance the overall graduate student experience, by advancing the university’s academic goals and promoting quality presentations and research efforts.

2023-2024 Committee Members

Haley Dawson, Legal Psychology (Doctoral Program)- CASE
GPSC Chair & Graduate Senator

 

Alejandro Arzola, Doctor of Medicine
GPSC Vice Chair, Medical Senator

 

Ahmed Soliman, Graduate Research Assistant, Ph.D. Candidate, ESRL, ECE, FIU
Graduate Senator

 

Sarwar Minar, Graduate Teaching Assistant, International Relations PhD, Dept of Politics, and International Relations- SIPA
Graduate Senator

 

Hossam Hussein, Graduate Research Assistant, ESRL, Dept. of ECE, CEC

Graduate Senator

 

Kanayo Nomeh, Graduate Teaching Assistant, International Relations PhD, Dept of Politics, and International Relations- SIPA
Graduate Senator

 

Ciara Jeneske, Juris Doctorate in Law
Law Senator

Name: Graham Center
Description: The Graham Center falls within the Division of Student Affairs. Graham Center Policies & Procedures are in compliance with University regulations and provide necessary guidelines to ensure that all GC events and activities are conducted with the highest level of safety, with civility and in an orderly fashion. For additional information on reserving our facilities, requesting services, event presentations, rental fee schedule or any questions you may have, please contact the staff at the Graham Center Office at GC1210 or call 305-348-2297.

Name: Green Campus Initiative
Description:
The Green Campus Initiative (GCI) is a student initiative aiming to develop and implement feasible plans to make FIU environmentally friendly.

Interested in joining? Fill out this short form!

Name: Green Energy Society
Description: The organization's main goal is to encourage the adoption and understanding of green energy sources. This is achieved through various means such as organizing informative talks, workshops, and constructive discussions focused on educating FIU students about these environmentally friendly energy options.

Name: H.E.A.L at FIU (Health Education for Aspiring Leaders)
Description: H.E.A.L at FIU (Health Education for Aspiring Leaders) is a non-profit, humanitarian, self-supported student organization whose goals are to educate aspiring healthcare professionals with the adequate community service, shadowing and leadership opportunities. We give our members the ability to gain experience, practice and develop the skills necessary for all disciplines in diverse fields of healthcare such as medical, nursing, dental, pharmaceutical, occupational therapy, etc.

Name: Haitian Student Union
Description: Haitian Student Union (HSU) is an organization on campus under the Council of Student Organizations, and is open to everyone. HSU seeks to unify all students of the Haitian diaspora here at FIU. HSU, via political, social, educational, and community service events, seeks to continue educating its constituents as well as the FIU community about the history, tradition, culture, present day progress of Haiti and matters pertaining to the Haitian diaspora. HSU strives not only to maintain the legacy which the Haitian forefathers have paved, but to also bridge the gap between the past, present and future generations of Haitians.

Name: Healing Hands
Description: Healing Hands is a club that helps ready students for their career path in the health and medical professions. This is a great opportunity not only for pre-health students to connect with each other, but also to work closely with a healthcare professional in their field of interest. The student is given the option to volunteer in multiple specialties including internal medicine, dentistry, neurology, OB/GYN, oncology, pediatrics, dermatology, pulmonology, triage, cardiology, optometry, pharmacy, and psychology/psychiatry. The club will meet to discuss organizations and nonprofits that they would like to help with during the duration of the club, as well as potential speakers who will help students better understand the career they are going into! Once a month the club will either go out into the community to help a chosen health and medical organization, or do an event to help raise money for organizations!

Name: Healthy Hearts
Description: N/A

Name: Healthy Living Program
Description:
Our on-campus services and online education promote the 7 Dimensions of Wellness: physical, intellectual, occupational, emotional, social, spiritual, and environmental. Stressed, can’t sleep, want to eat better, or just want to be healthier? Our services cover a variety of your wellness needs. Explore the many different on campus opportunities below to Relax, Feel Good, and Be Well.

  • Health Consultations
  • Massage Therapy
  • Aromatherapy
  • Acupuncture
  • HIV Testing
  • Sexual Health Resources
  • Energy Therapy
  • Dietitian Services
  • Student Food Pantry

Name: HEARTbeats A Cappella
Description:
Florida International University’s Award-Winning All Gender A Cappella Group. This group consists of talented singers of all skill levels and backgrounds. The members of HEARTbeats have majors in a variety of focuses from prelaw and premed to architecture and the arts.

HEARTbeats performs all around campus for events like ROARthon, which raises funds for cancer research, and performs off campus at organizations like EasterSeals, a home for the elderly. We also perform every year at the International Competition of Collegiate A Cappella (ICCA).

Name: HEARTS Art Club
Description: Founded in Fall 2015 by Cynthia Piorno and Professor Gretchen Sharnagl, the HEARTS Art Club offers a judgement-free zone where members can express themselves freely through a variety of media. It is currently led by Cate McGinnis. Lounge with us as we listen to music and do what we do best: make art!

Name: HEARTS Crochet Club
Description: The purpose of this organization shall be to establish a welcoming and supportive environment for individuals who share a passion for various yarn crafts. Our primary focus is crocheting, however, we embrace other yarn-related activities like knitting and embroidery. We intend to provide tutorials for beginners, while also introducing complex projects to challenge our experienced members. In addition to our regular themed meetings, we will be hosting events that allow our members to showcase their handcrafted creations!

Name: Hearts for the Homeless Miami
Description: N/A

Name: HEARTS Photo Club
Description:
-Established on October 13th, 2017.

-We are a club under FIU Honors College “HEARTS” (Honors Education in the Arts)

-Open to Honors College and Non-Honors College FIU Students. Everyone is welcome here!

-We specialize in Digital Photography and Mobile Photography

-All our meetings for the Fall 2023 semester will be Hybrid on Thursdays from 6:00 PM to 7:00 PM (Biweekly). Room: TBA

-The main communication channels are our organization's email fiuheartsphoto@gmail.com and our WhatsApp group chat.

 

Make sure to fill out this Google Form to become an official member

Name: HEARTS Shakespeare Society
Description: Some people think that the plays of William Shakespeare are dull, confusing relics of the past. HEARTS Shakespeare Society hopes to bring the drama, romance, chaos, and laughter of Shakespeare’s plays to a modern audience. This club allows members to enjoy Shakespeare not as an assignment but as a work of entertainment. Join us for an hour of revels so fun it will make parting such sweet sorrow!

Name: HEARTS Writing Club
Description:
Hearts Writing Club allows students to collaborate and share their unique stories and creative works in a safe and welcoming environment. At every meeting, students will engage with a theme/prompt and produce creative written works that they may choose to share with peers in a friendly environment. Students may use any type of writing style they prefer. Open to all FIU majors, Honors and Non – Honors alike.

Join our Whatsapp chat for updates!!

https://chat.whatsapp.com/BiSVAr68QsY8fo6oTPfyEX

Name: Herpetology Club
Description: The Herpetology Club at Florida International University is an academic and social-based student organization aimed at sharing and promoting an appreciation for the field of herpetology, animal husbandry, and Florida’s ecosystems. We host a variety of events focused on herpetology (reptiles & amphibians), such as educational lectures, networking opportunities, fundraisers, field trips, and more!

Name: Higher Education Student Association - H.E.S.A.
Description: We, the members of Higher Education Student Association (H.E.S.A.), hereby associate ourselves to foster a working and learning environment among undergraduate and graduate students pursuing a career or have an interest in higher education. H.E.S.A. provides opportunities for academic, professional, and social development to enhance students’ knowledge of the profession and to make students more well-rounded professionals. H.E.S.A. also strives to work with other university officials to advocate for the betterment of students and serve as mentors to undergraduate students who are interested in higher education.

Name: Hillel
Description:
Hillel at FIU is a student organization that provides opportunities to explore and celebrate Judaism and Jewish culture. We provide a positive, engaging atmosphere through religious, educational, cultural, social, and community service programming. In addition, Hillel strives to promote social justice and Israel awareness.

Our mission is to enrich the lives of Jewish students so that they can in turn enrich the Jewish community in Miami and around the world.

Name: Hindu Students Council
Description: HSC will promote and showcase Hindu culture at FIU. This is an effort to recognize the diversity that exists here by fostering an appreciation for and understanding of the lifestyles and customs of Hinduism. We welcome all students to join.

Name: Homecoming Council
Description: Homecoming Council is an organization that works with many other organizations and departments to plan a week of activities for FIU. FIU's Homecoming Week consists of many exciting events such as: Panthermonium, Homecoming Court activities, Panthers Got Talent, The Uncaging, the Parade, and a showcase of Panther Spirit!

Name: Immigrant Scholars Organization
Description: Immigrant Scholars Organization is an organization at FIU for immigrant and non-immigrant students interested in migration studies. Our goal is to encourage FIU immigrant students to continue their studies in higher education by providing them with resources, knowledge, and a community that would support them emotionally. We are dedicated to educating the FIU community about the current issues affecting the immigrant community in the United States and celebrating immigrants’ contributions to our society by coordinating informative and cultural events that enrich campus life.

Name: Indian Students Association
Description: We are a student organization working towards propagating the culture, traditions, and arts of India at FIU. In a fast paste and diverse city like Miami we feel it is necessary to unite participating members, both of Indian origin and interested non-Indians, and expose our great culture to our community. Our main goal is to serve as a providing organization for our school, students, faculty, and community. We hope to enable these people to enjoy, appreciate, and be a part of our rich and colorful heritage. Throughout the years ISA has conducted various events ranging from our annual Holi event, movie nights, picnics, Indian parties, and much more. An important aspect of our organization is to network with other clubs, schools, and community associations to build strong relationships with them. We feel this is important in maintaining unity among our community. ISA also assists international students coming to our country for the first time.

Name: Industrial-Organizational Psychology Club
Description: The purpose of this organization shall be to enhance industrial-organizational psychology awareness for students at FIU, provide them with collaborative research and applied opportunities, and encourage, prepare, and support those who wish to pursue a career in the field by applying to graduate programs.

Name: Infectious Disease Interest Group
Description: N/A

Name: Innovative Medicine Technology Interest Group
Description: N/A

Name: Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers at FIU
Description: The IEEE at FIU Student Branch can be a very positive element throughout student's academic career, offering a variety of programs, activities, professional careers and talent development opportunities that allow students to network their critical skills outside of a college classroom. In order to nurture that development, the IEEE Branch At FIU offers a multitude of workshops, project meetings and information sessions from companies that allow a student to really learn the technical skills that are required in their respective engineering industries, but to explore and understand what the future can hold in the engineering disciplines.

Name: Institute of Transportation Engineers
Description: The purpose of this organization shall be to promote the advancement of transportation engineering, foster the closer association of students with the transportation profession and the Institute of Transportation Engineers (ITE), to promote the development of professional spirit, and to identify and address common transportation interests among the student members.

Name: Interfraternity Council
Description:
The aims of The Interfraternity Council of Florida International University are to promote and perpetuate the best interests of the Greek Letter social fraternities under our council. To encourage the most complete intellectual, emotional, physical and social development of the members of the fraternities. To ensure that the fraternities chartered at Florida International University establish and maintain high standards and lofty pursuits and to foster cooperation among all organizations, university officials and the community.

 

The Interfraternity Council of Florida International University does not discriminate on the basis of age, color, race, national or ethnic origin, religion, sexual orientation or disability.

 

It shall be the purpose of this Council to:

A. Act as the supervising and advising body of all North-American Interfraternity Conference (NIC) and other non National Pan-Hellenic Council recognized social fraternities.

B. Organize, standardize and regulate the recruitment and new member activities of said fraternities.

C. Promote positive Interfraternity competition in scholarship, service, athletics, and other events that may be deemed advisable for the betterment of the participants, fraternities, the University, and the community.

D. Encourage cooperation and harmony among fraternities.

E. Provide educational programs and services for the member fraternities.

F. Serve as the liaison between the University authorities and member fraternities in matters of common interest.

G. Act as a judicial body for violations of the FIU Student Conduct Code and the Interfraternity Council policies.

 

Welcome to the Interfraternity Council Forum!

Name: Internal Medicine Interest Group
Description: N/A

Name: International Art and Design Club
Description:
The International Art & Design Club at FIU promotes knowledge and collaboration in the graphic arts and related fields. IAD's goal is to meet, network, enjoy, and learn. We will have movie nights, games, lectures, workshops, and hands-on creative events! This is a great opportunity to meet other visual designers who will share insights on the next big step in your careers as creatives.

No Membership fee is required to JOIN!

To join, simply send us an email or reach out to us on Panther Connect or Instagram.

Name: InterVarsity Christian Fellowship - MMC
Description: We encourage and equip students and faculty to follow Christ as they seek to be a redeeming influence among the people, ideas, and structures of the university and professions. We offer Bible study and other groups at the undergraduate and graduate levels, including fellowship for Medical and Law students.

Name: Intramural Soccer Club @ FIU
Description: Our club will take pleasure in providing a friendly environment where everyone can participate in the beautiful game both on and off the field, without the need for any prior experience. In addition to the traditional matches, we will provide a variety of soccer-related activities including movie screenings, trivia evenings, FIFA gaming sessions, training sessions, and other activities. Our mission is to broaden the horizons of soccer fans by providing a comprehensive experience that extends beyond the pitch.

Name: Italian Club @ FIU
Description:
Here at the FIU Italian Club, our goal is to spread Italian culture and cuisine, while expanding our Italian conversational skills and sharing our experiences and passion for the Italian language and culture.

Join our WhatsApp group chat here:FIU Italian Groupchat Link

Name: Jack D. Gordon Institute for Public Policy
Description: FIU’s Jack D. Gordon Institute for Public Policy was founded in 1985 to establish, promote, and advance the study of public policy and national security studies. The institute serves as the forefront of public policy discourse by leading, integrating, and delivering exceptional multidisciplinary education and research while improving the competitiveness and diversity of students and professionals entering the workforce. The institute is centered on four pillars: Academics, Executive Education, Research, and Community Outreach, each serving the mission of shaping public policy and national security solutions in the 21st century.

Name: Jamaican Student Union
Description: N/A

Name: Japan Club
Description:
A fun place to learn about Japan through discussions, events, games, socials and films.

Join us on WhatsApp and Discord!

Name: Jewish Medical Student Association
Description: N/A

Name: Kappa Delta Pi International Honor Society In Education
Description: The purpose of the Omicron Theta Chapter of Kappa Delta Pi shall be to promote excellence in and recognition of outstanding contributions to education and education related majors at FIU. Kappa Delta Pi shall endeavor to maintain a high degree of professional fellowship among its members, to quicken professional growth, and to honor achievement in educational work.  To these ends, it shall invite to membership persons who exhibit commendable professional qualities, worth educational ideals, and sound scholarship, without regard to race, age, ethnicity, religion, gender or sexual identity, or disability.

Name: Kappa Sigma
Description: Kappa Sigma, is an international fraternity with currently 307 active chaptersNorth America. Kappa Sigma has initiated more than 290,000 men on college campuses throughout the United States and Canada. Today, the Fraternity has over 196,000 living alumni and more than 16,000 undergraduate members. In 2012, the Fraternity "pledged more men than any other fraternity in history."It is one of the leaders of all American fraternities in terms of pledges and new initiates per year, service hours, and philanthropic donations. Its endowment fund, founded in 1919 is the oldest college fraternity foundation and has donated more than $6.5 million to undergrads since 1948. In 2012 alone, the Fraternity's endowment fund raised over $1 million in donations.

Name: Kendo Club
Description: FIUKC aims to help members improve themselves in body and mind through the practice of kendo. Kendo is a traditional Japanese martial arts which teaches the use of the katana through analogues such as the shinai (bamboo sword) and bokken (solid wood sword). Kendokas, students of Kendo, wear dark blue armor called bogu which embodies the spirit of old yoroi armor like that worn by samurai. Want to join the FIUKC family and start your journey?

Name: Kesem at Florida International University
Description: Kesem is a nationwide community, driven by passionate college student leaders, that supports children through and beyond their parent’s cancer. Kesem is the largest national organization dedicated to supporting children impacted by a parent’s cancer, at no cost to families. Our innovative and fun-filled programs provide children with peers who understand their unique needs, and create long-lasting impact.

Name: Korean Culture Club
Description: Our mission is to share our love and knowledge of Korean culture with students who are interested in learning and immersing themselves in Korean culture. We hope to increase the student body's knowledge on modern and traditional Korean history, language, art, pop culture, global relations, and more. We plan to spread awareness of Korean culture to our members through entertaining and informative activities. This club will be a way for all to meet and learn together about a culture that captivates us! We look forward to having a great time with you all!

Name: Korean Language Empowerment Club
Description: The mission of the Korean Language Empowerment Club (KLEC) is to help you acquire a job, internship, or acceptance into a graduate or study abroad program. Our goal is to strengthen your Korean language skills through weekly tutoring sessions.The program will cover topics such as TOPIK, TEFL, and more.

Name: La Unidad Latina, Lambda Upsilon Lambda Fraternity, Inc.
Description: La Unidad Latina, Lambda Upsilon Lambda Fraternity, Incorporated was established on February 19, 1982 in order to address the shortcomings of academic institutions in meeting and addressing the needs of Latino and underrepresented students in higher education. LUL is an organization that professionally promotes the goals and standards that it has set for itself. Our track record speaks for itself as recognized and awarded by our peers locally and nationally. We do not pride ourselves of merely being the first or the largest, we pride ourselves in being the best. Lambda Upsilon Lambda challenges individuals to think before making a decision. We don't tell men they belong with us, those who aspire to be LEADERS know where to find us. The Alpha Rho Chapter was founded in 2004 when 3 devoted gentlemen pledged and became the Founding brothers of LUL at Florida International University. After breaking ground in the state of Florida, Alpha Rho chapter has worked diligently to bring awareness of the fraternity’s goals which are to reinforce the importance of education, provide a positive image for our community, and bring minority issues to the forefront.

Name: Lacrosse - W
Description: We are a club team where girls can come to play lacrosse. We practice Monday and Wednesday 9:00-10:45pm at South Turf (right across the street from the gym). We play games all year round. No experience is needed to join. If you have never played before, do not worry we will teach you. Come and join us at practice!

Name: Lakeview North
Description:
• Refrigerator
  • Laundry room on 1st floor of Lakeview North
  • Twin mattress (size 36 x 74 x 6)
  • Shared bathroom
  • Meal plan included in rent

Name: Lakeview South
Description:
• Refrigerator
  • Laundry room on 1st floor of Lakeview North
  • Twin mattress (size 36 x 74 x 6)
  • Shared bathroom
  • Meal plan included in rent

Name: Lambda Theta Alpha Latin Sorority, Inc.
Description:
Welcome to the Panther Connect page of the Gamma Pi Chapter of Lambda Theta Alpha Latin Sorority, Incorporated at Florida International University.

LTA was founded at Kean University in Union, New Jersey in 1975. Since then, it has successfully served as a support group for women and minorities within the community, university, and personal/professional life. We are an organization of strong and determined people, living through our principles of Unity, Love, and Respect. We strive to impact the community and our lifelong sisterhood in a life-changing way.

Lambda Theta Alpha is proudly the FIRST and LARGEST Latin sorority in the nation, yet is “Latin by Tradition, not by Definition,” welcoming all ethnicities and backgrounds.

Name: Latin American Dance Club
Description:
Welcome to Latin American Dance Club, the vibrant and inclusive organization that celebrates the joy of dance and the richness of Latin American culture! Whether you're a beginner or an experienced dancer, this club is your home to learn, dance, and embrace the lively rhythms of Latin America. Our purpose is to create a welcoming space where students from all backgrounds can come together, have fun, and explore the diverse world of social dances while immersing themselves in the captivating tapestry of Latin American traditions. The best part is that our regular dance classes are free of charge!

 

 

What We Offer:

1. Dance Workshops: We host regular free dance workshops led by skilled instructors who are passionate about sharing their knowledge of Latin dances. From salsa to merengue, bachata to rumba, we cover a wide range of dance styles that will get your feet moving and your spirits soaring.

 

 

2. Social Dancing Events: Put those new moves to the test! Join our exciting social dance events where you can practice with fellow club members and let loose on the dance floor. Don't worry about your skill level; everyone is here to have fun and support each other's journey in dance.

 

 

3. Cultural Immersion: Beyond the dance floor, we take pride in sharing the vibrant heritage of Latin American culture. You’ll gain a deeper understanding and appreciation of Latin America’s rich traditions and customs through special cultural events, movie nights, guest speakers, and more.

 

 

4. Community Outreach: Latin American Dance Club believes in giving back to the broader university community. We actively participate in campus events and collaborate with other student organizations to promote diversity, unity, and cultural exchange.

 

 

Why Join Us?

- All Levels Welcome: We encourage everyone to join us whether you’re an absolute beginner or an experienced dancer. Our friendly and supportive atmosphere ensures that everyone feels comfortable and valued.

 

 

- Have Fun and Stay Active: Dancing is not just about mastering steps; it's about letting go, embracing the music, and having a blast. Get ready to dance your worries away and stay active in a fun and engaging way.

 

 

- Expand Your Social Circle: Latin American Dance Club is a place to forge lasting friendships and connections with students who share your passion for dance and culture. You'll find a warm and diverse community that will make your university experience even more fulfilling.

 

 

- Celebrate Diversity: By joining our club, you become a part of a larger movement to celebrate the rich cultural heritage of Latin American communities. Embrace diversity and learn about the world through dance and shared experiences.

 

 

Don't miss out on the opportunity to join the Latin American Dance Club and be a part of this dynamic and welcoming community. Let's dance, learn, and share the joy of Latin American culture together! Everyone is welcome, so join us for an unforgettable journey of rhythm and unity. ¡Bienvenidos al Club de Baile Latinoamericano! (Welcome to Latin American Dance Club!)

Name: Latino America Unida, Lambda Alpha Upsilon Fraternity, Inc.
Description: The mission of Latino America Unida, Lambda Alpha Upsilon Fraternity, Inc. is to be a network of professionals that promotes brotherhood, scholarship and service to the community. The fraternity promotes brotherhood by providing its members personal and professional support on an undergraduate and alumni level. Our members pursue scholarship not only for professional advancement, but to attain personal growth. The brotherhood serves the community by sponsoring events which aide those in need, promoting cultural awareness, and enriching the collegiate environment. Every member must continue to uphold the mission and goals of the fraternity, as they are the common values that distinguish us as Hermanos of Lambda Alpha Upsilon.

Name: Latino Medical Student Association
Description: N/A

Name: Le Cercle Francais
Description: Le Cercle Français is an organization which thrives on assimilating French culture into everyday life and gives students the opportunity to learn both a different language and take part in interesting events and community service projects.

Name: Little Passengers
Description: The purpose of Little Passengers is to support underserved youth in Latin American countries through conducting neuroscience and environmental research. Our three upcoming projects are planned to be done in Venezuela. They will include aiding in children's neurodevelopment while working on sustainable communities. Little Passengers’ purpose as an FIU Chapter is to bring together a group of FIU students, faculty, and alumni to work towards completing Little Passengers’ mission through general body meetings, socials, and fundraisers. Our mission is to improve the neurological development of children as well as the health of the environment through sustainable projects in the communities we'll be working in. We envision that this will allow children to have an equal opportunity to grow in a healthy environment that meets all their needs while creating thriving communities that work towards a greener and more sustainable earth.

Name: Logistics and Supply Chain Management Association at FIU
Description: Greetings Panthers! The Logistics and Supply Chain Management Association is FIU's first student organization dedicated solely to the Logistics and Supply Chain Management field. Our purpose is to educate students interested in the field of Logistics and Supply Chain Management through real life practices, so that they will have the knowledge and skills to become a professional in the field, or any area of interest that has a logistical and supply chain management component to it. Individuals from any industry are encouraged to join our organization! In addition to tackling their logistics and supply chain management skills, members are given the opportunity to meet and connect with each other as well as industry professionals.

Name: LUMI Interest Group
Description: N/A

Name: Male Mentoring Initiative
Description:
Male Mentoring Initiative seeks to develop male college students using a curriculum model. These points include: Nurture Diversity, Global Engagement, Civic Responsibility and Commitment, and Academic Success. This program provides the support strategies that fosters retention and higher graduation rates.

Male Mentoring Initiative goal is to empower our students through mentoring, personal/professional maturity through meaningful interaction. Our students will develop an understanding of their own masculinity that is not prescribed to them by negative conceptions of what it means to be a man.

Name: Maurice A. Ferré Institute for Civic Leadership
Description: Mayor Ferré gave his heart and his life to serving alongside the people of Miami. His legacy extends far beyond our city of the future to the very heart of democracy-the people. A true statesman, he mobilized civic leaders and citizens, governed a city and a county across racial divides and evolving demographics, and advanced innovative policies and programs that will improve the quality of life for generations to come. The Maurice A. Ferré Institute for Civic Leadership builds on his legacy, preparing FIU students and the members of the public who will effect positive social change in local and global communities.

Name: Medically Engaged Diverse Students
Description: The mission of Medically Engaged Diverse Students is to support fellow undergraduate students interested in the field of medicine. The purpose of Medically Engaged Diverse Students is to help students increase their chances of being accepted into medical and PA school by providing research, shadowing, community service and MCAT practice opportunities. But most importantly, we are trying to increase students' commitment in our society by assisting those in need in our local community. Functions of the organization include inviting doctors to speak at our meetings, partaking in community service events, providing shadowing opportunities to students, organizing the medical mentoring event, encouraging collaboration between students, and motivating students to take on leadership roles.

Name: Meteorology Club at FIU
Description:
The mission of the organization is to educate the members and the student at Florida International University about meteorological topics including, but not limited to: weather, climatology, physics applicable to meteorology, current atmospheric events, major areas of research, new technological innovations, recent discoveries, notable individuals within the field, certification programs, and potential career opportunities in the private sector.

The purpose of the organization will be achieved by holding lectures open to FIU students, faculty, and staff, as well as organizing club outings and activities designed for the enrichment and engagement of students with their local communities.

Name: Mock Trial at FIU
Description: It shall be the mission of this organization to provide all FIU students with the opportunity and skill set to excel in the area of trial advocacy. It is the responsibility of this organization to offer its participants the knowledge that will put them ahead of their competitors across scads of professional fields. This is to be done primarily through educational seminars and mock trial competitions in which each member enhances, polishes, and perfects his or her abilities to ensure the greatest possibility for professional advancement. By doing this, we, the members of Mock Trial at FIU, take on a responsibility to our participants, our academic institution, and our community at large; a responsibility to insure a better world tomorrow by properly education brighter minds today.

Name: Multicultural Greek Council
Description:
The Multicultural Greek Council (MGC) is the governing body for Florida International University's culturally-based fraternities and sororities. Since its founding on January 23, 2008, the MGC has been committed to fostering and maintaining an inclusive, diverse, and welcoming environment for students of all backgrounds. The MGC promotes global awareness and inclusivity through its programming efforts, values, presence, and overall impact on students. By advocating for equity and justice, members strengthen relationships among themselves and motivate one another to continue living out their fraternal and sororal values.

 

Lambda Theta Alpha Latin Sorority, Inc.

La Unidad Latina, Lambda Upsilon Lambda Fraternity, Inc.

Latino America Unida, Lambda Alpha Upsilon Fraternity, Inc. 

Sigma Lambda Beta International Fraternity, Inc.

Sigma Lambda Gamma National Sorority, Inc.

Theta Nu Xi Multicultural Sorority, Inc.

 

 

Interested in learning more? Visit our website!

Name: Multifaith Council
Description:
Our motto: unity in diversity. A collaborative endeavor of various, independent religious organizations, the FIU-MFC exists to:

(a) Promote mutual understanding, respect, appreciation, and cooperation among people of faith within the University community;

(b) Advocate for the pursuit of truth in a climate of open inquiry;

(c) Serve as a gateway for individuals to access campus services, thereby sharing with the University a commitment to the holistic development of individuals;

(d) Foster spiritual values that lead to human flourishing.

Name: Music & Medicine Interest Group
Description: N/A

Name: Music Art and Design @ FIU
Description:
The purpose of this organization shall be to, serve as a club to help connect creatives through social/online networking opportunities such as events, performances, shows, displaying, exhibits or any place where creatives apart and not apart the club can connect.

 

A community where displaying creative projects can reach an audience, network with likeminded individuals, learn from various creative mediums and socialize over artistry. Future networking opportunities with professionals in the field(s).

Name: Muslim Students Association
Description: Assalamu Alaikum! (Peace Be Upon You!) The goal of the Muslim Student Association at Florida International University (referred to as MSA at FIU) is to create a stronger bond among Muslims in and around the South Florida area. We wish to provide correct and authentic information, for both Muslims and non-Muslims, regarding true Islamic theology (Aqeedah) and the Fundamentals of our Faith (Arkan al-Islam). We also aim to provide a safe haven for Muslims on campus, as well as provide an outlet for Muslims to meet each other. Through our endeavors, we hope not only to dispel any false and derogatory ideas towards Islam and Muslims but also to spread the true word and preach the Grace and Mercy of Allah. Indeed, Allah knows best. MSA at FIU is also responsible for: * Promoting unity and joint action among the Muslims on-campus, off-campus and in the surrounding communities. * Conducting social, religious and other activities in accordance with the best traditions of Islam. * Arranging and holding congregational prayers and Islamic religious festivals at appropriate times. * Promoting friendly relations between Muslims and non-Muslims. * Endeavoring to make Islamic teachings known to interested non-Muslims. * Respecting and upholding Islamic values.

Name: National Association of Hispanic Journalists BBC
Description: Provide networking opportunities for Hispanic journalism students. Contribute the recognition and professional advancement of Hispanics in the news industry.

Name: National Organization of Minority Architecture Students at FIU
Description: N/A

Name: National Pan-Hellenic Council
Description:
The National Pan-Hellenic Council (NPHC) also referred to as "Divine 9" is the governing body for Florida International University's 9 historically Black fraternities and sororities. These organizations were established under the premise of academic and social support to ensure student success and community uplift. The NPHC’s purpose is to promote unity and expose members to the “service for life” philosophy and foster leadership development and scholarship. Furthermore, the NPHC promotes interaction through forums, meetings and other mediums for the exchange of information and engages in cooperative programming and initiatives through various activities and functions.

 

Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Inc.

Name: National Society of Black Engineers
Description: NSBE's mission is to increase the number of culturally responsible black engineers who excel academically, succeed professionally and positively impact the community. Listed below are some of the various objectives of NSBE FIU chapter. - To simulate and develop student interest in the various engineering, science technology and mathematics disciplines - To increase the number of minority students in these disciplines at both the undergraduate and graduate levels - To encourage members to seek advanced degrees in engineering or related fields or STEM majors and obtain professional engineering registration - To promote public awareness of engineering and the opportunities for minorities in the profession - To encourage and advise minority youths in their pursuit of an engineering career. - To function as a representative body on issues and development that affects the careers of minority engineers

Name: National Society of Collegiate Scholars
Description: The National Society of Collegiate Scholars (NSCS) is an honors organization that recognizes and elevates high achievers and accepts students from all majors. NSCS provides career and graduate school connections, leadership and service opportunities and gives out a million dollars in scholarships annually. Members are deeply committed to scholarship, leadership and service and as a result, are impacting their campus and local communities every day.

Name: National Student Exchange Club
Description: Become a part of an exhilarating and culturally enriching club. Meet students from all around the world! All FIU students are welcome to come to our club meetings and events!

Name: National Student Speech Language Hearing Association
Description:
We are the FIU chapter of the National Student Speech Language Hearing Association: An organization dedicated to working together as pre-professionals studying CSD to be better prepared for life after the degree. We:

  • Unite students interested in communication sciences and disorders 
  • Ensure that students have access to resources and information to succeed in the field of audiology, speech pathology and speech-hearing research
  • Provide opportunities for networking, enhancing knowledge, community service, fundraising and volunteer work
  • Contribute to the local South Florida community with fundraisers and volunteering opportunities
  • Source guest speakers to give us a glimpse into the life of a Speech-Language Pathologist

Name: Navigators
Description:
The Navigators is a Christian organization that is all about helping students connect with God and each other. Our motto is to Know Christ, Make Him Know, and Help Others do the Same. We are a group open to all people to enjoy relationship with one another and explore the Bible. We do this through small group Bible studies every week and life-to-life discipleship. 

We have an international student ministry as well! We come alongside students that come to FIU from all around the world. We help students learn english, have fun events around Miami, and engage in meaningful friendships.

Name: Nepalese Student Association-FIU
Description: The Nepalese Student Association (NSA-FIU) is a student organization at [Florida International University] that brings together Nepalese students to create a supportive community. Through a variety of activities and events, NSA aims to celebrate Nepalese culture, promote academic success, and foster social connections among all the students in the University. From cultural festivals to educational workshops, NSA provides a platform for Nepalese students to thrive academically and socially while away from  homeland.

Name: Nu Rho Psi
Description:
Nu Rho Psi is the National Honor Society in Neuroscience, founded in 2006 by the Faculty for Undergraduate Neuroscience. Our Delta of Florida Chapter at Florida International University was founded in 2022. We are an independent non-profit, grass-roots organization comprised of neuroscientists, like you.

 

The purpose of Nu Rho Psi is to encourage professional interest and excellence in scholarship, particularly in neuroscience; award recognition to students who have achieved such excellence in scholarship; advance the discipline of neuroscience; encourage intellectual and social interaction between students, faculty, and professionals in neuroscience and related fields; promote career development in neuroscience and related fields; increase public awareness of neuroscience and its benefits for the individual and society; and encourage service to the community.

 

For more information, visit www.nurhopsi.org or contact us at nurhopsi@fiu.edu.

Name: Obstetrics and Gynecology Interest Group
Description: N/A

Name: OE Honors College EdgeLab
Description: We are a makerspace lab available to everyone in the FIU community located in OE 165. We have multiple machines that guests can use, or learn to use.

Name: Office of Engagement
Description: FIU's Office of Engagement serves as a partner in collaboration to its community, faculty, and students. Through community partnerships, public private partnerships, multi-stakeholder coalitions, and leading in assists, the Office of Engagement is able to work with its stakeholders and unite collective resources to embrace the most complex challenges in the community and create impact, hope and opportunity.

Name: Office of Global Indigenous Forum
Description:
With the Indigenous leadership of the Global Indigenous Forum, the vision is for FIU to be known as a welcoming institution for Indigenous faculty, staff, students, and Indigenous peoples from local, regional and worldwide communities.

Recognizing our common values for land, territory, cultural preservation, a good life, and all our relations, through engaged partnerships and collaborations our mutual efforts focus on the issues and perspectives of Indigenous peoples locally and worldwide.

Through GIF efforts FIU will be recognized globally as a place for Indigenous issues to be openly and fairly discussed through courses, dialogs, conferences, media, exhibits, research publications, and engaged action-oriented activities.

Name: Office of Social Justice and Inclusion
Description:
The Office of Social Justice & Inclusion works with students, faculty, and staff to:
  • Empower social change;
  • Advocate for diversity and inclusion;
  • Educate for justice and equity; and
  • Act with empathy and impact. 

Our team encourages Panthers to engage with us through the following programs, services, and resources: 

  • Annual MLK Commemorative Celebration;
  • Fundamentals of Social Badge Program;
  • EVERFI Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion Training Program; 
  • Inclusive Language Guide; 
  • Male Mentoring Initiative;
  • Pride Center;
  • Programs on Demand;
  • and Women's Center

Name: Office of Student Conduct and Academic Integrity
Description: Student Conduct and Academic Integrity serves Florida International University by educating community members about the Student Conduct and Honor Code and the value of respecting others. Through the student conduct process, we hold students accountable for their behavior in a fair and developmental manner while upholding the rights of the community.

Name: Office of the Ombudsperson
Description: The Ombudsperson provides assistance to students who have encountered problems or conflicts within the university. Particularly problems not being adequately addressed through normal channels. The Ombudsperson may resolve problems through various methods, including making inquiries or referrals to the appropriate university department for review. The Ombuds empowers individuals to overcome disputes, conflicts and barriers that stand in the way of reaching their full potential.

Name: Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Inc.
Description:
Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Inc. is the first international fraternal organization founded on the campus of a historically black college. Omega Psi Phi was founded at Howard University located in Washington, D.C. The founders were three undergraduates -- Edgar Amos Love, Oscar James Cooper and Frank Coleman. Joining them was their faculty adviser, Ernest Everett Just.

From the initials of the Greek phrase meaning, "friendship is essential to the soul", the name Omega Psi Phi was derived. That phrase was selected as the motto.

Manhood, Scholarship, Perseverance and Uplift were adopted as Cardinal Principles.

Name: Omicron Delta Kappa
Description: Omicron Delta Kappa, the National Leadership Honor Society, was founded December 3, 1914, at Washington and Lee University in Lexington, Virginia by 15 student and faculty leaders. The founders formulated the idea that leadership of exceptional quality and versatility in college should be recognized, that representatives in all phases of college life should cooperate in worthwhile endeavors, and that outstanding students, faculty, and administrators should meet on a basis of mutual interest, understanding, and helpfulness. ODK® was the first college honor society of a national scope to give recognition and honor for meritorious leadership and service in extracurricular activities and to encourage the development of general campus citizenship. Since its founding, Omicron Delta Kappa has initiated over 300,000 members. The Society recognizes achievement in the following five areas: * Scholarship * Athletics * Campus/ Community Service, Social/Religious Activities, and Campus Government * Journalism, Speech and the Mass Media * Creative and Performing Arts.

Name: Oncology Interest Group
Description: N/A

Name: Order of Omega
Description: N/A

Name: Order of the Torch
Description: From a single building on what once was an abandoned airfield in southwest Miami-Dade County, plans were crafted in 1969 for the formation of what would become one of the largest universities in the country. Because of these unlikely beginnings, Florida International University has established itself as an anchor institution in South Florida by solving some of the greatest challenges of our time. FIU is dedicated to enriching the lives of the local and global community. Such organizational greatness is the result of the decades-long devotion of many devoted individuals. In 2003, a group of Panthers sought to establish a high honor that would pay homage to the work of the institution’s greatest contributors – past, present, and future. The Order of the Torch is comprised of students, faculty, administrators/staff, alumni, and other devotees who have distinguished themselves as contributors to the greater university community and remain vested in the continued development and enhancement of FIU.

Name: Organization Advisors
Description: N/A

Name: Orientation and Family Programs
Description: Whether it's through mandatory First-Year or Transfer Orientation, Panther Camp, family programming, or any of the other exciting initiatives we provide, they all seek to set you up for a successful and rewarding college experience. We are a resource for your transition to campus and throughout your college career!

Name: Orthopedic Surgery and Sports Medicine Interest Group
Description: N/A

Name: Outdoor Club
Description: The purpose of this organization is to facilitate and practice safe outdoor adventures for all FIU students. To familiarize FIU students with the exciting activities that can be found in our revolving environment and facilitate the development of stronger connections to nature and outdoor adventures.

Name: Pakistani Students Association
Description: The Pakistani Students Association at Florida International University is dedicated to spreading the teachings of its culture to those who wish to attain a diverse educational experience. We strive to create an environment where each individual feels comfortable in his/her own skin and is able to identify a home within a South Asian community. As a populous, multiethnic community, the PSA aspires to bring all students together to experience the cultures and teachings of this diverse country.

Name: Panther Aero (American Institute of Aeronautics & Astronautics)
Description:
We are a group of students from Florida International University (FIU) who are passionate about Aerospace Engineering. Although most of our members belong to Mechanical and Computer Engineering, we welcome students from all disciplines. By joining our club you will have the opportunity to work hand in hand with other engineers and apply many engineering principles to real world problems. You will also learn to work in a team-based environment and meet our dedicated members. 

Join our Discord!

https://discord.gg/XkUG57kzNP

Name: Panther Bionics
Description: Panther Bionics is a multidisciplinary engineering student organization that seeks to bring together passionate and curious undergraduate and graduate engineering students to cultivate research ideas and different projects within the diverse fields of Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Math (STEAM). Panther Bionics was established by the persistent and constant need to  integrate and join different disciplines in engineering , similar to a company which incorporates the use of all of its workers skills to complete tasks while simultaneously improving different aspects in which the worker may not excel in .  The organization aims to inspire, educate and empower student members by creating an environment that promotes creativity, innovation, and vision. The Multidisciplinary Engineering fields include biomedical engineering , mechanical engineering , electrical engineering , computer science and computer engineering and many more. Panther Bionics looks to bring all STEAM disciplines together to show the students how important each area (i.e. Music, Architecture, Math) can be to medical technology innovation. Multidisciplinary collaboration enables the students to work in teams to tackle the complex layers of  engineering projects , accelerates development of knowledge, skills, networks, and experiences to prepare its members for their future careers. The main objective of Panther Bionics is to engage undergraduate student members in problem solving and design activities , similar to the senior design concepts ,  throughout the year, and complete engineering- based projects that could potentially be presented at national and international competitions.  The educational components of the organization encompass learning and practicing translational research techniques, acquiring industry related skills such as design and prototyping, quality control and testing procedures, and more.  It also aids in helping students gain more exposure  to and experience in their respective fields before entering the work-place in the form of volunteering , outreach events and possible internships and career building activities such as workshops. Panther Bionics proposes a structured platform to educate the student body about the critical "bedside to bench to bedside" approach to Biomedical innovation which incorporates the use of all disciplines in engineering . This approach is a repeating loop of research-based medical care, in which clinical (bedside) observations stimulate research efforts (bench), which leads back to the bedside for implementation and further clinical discovery. Panther Bionics will act as a stepping stone for students to take their efforts to the next level by establishing a link with industry partners.  Panther Bionics will also aid in students gaining leadership and public speaking experience as students will essentially be put into teams to complete different tasks.

Name: Panther Christian Life
Description: Panther Christian Life's purpose is to share the saving Message of Christ’s Salvation to the FIU community (Mark 16:15). We seek to make disciples on campus that would be able to reach the nations for Christ (Matthew 28:19-20). Our focus will be on encouraging and inspiring individuals to cultivate their relationship with Jesus Christ, and to train and equip believers to live out the Great Commission in their lives (Acts 1:8, 2 Timothy 2:2). We aim to serve the Body of Christ on campus, in accordance with Acts 2:42-47.

Name: Panther Esports
Description:
Panther Esports seeks to create an organized environment for competitive video games at FIU. We will represent FIU in national collegiate Esports competitions, and host competitive events. We intend to give everybody interested in playing multiplayer video games a place to meet others with similar interests.

If you are interested, please join our Discord Server! Please fill out this form once you have joined the discord server to be verified as a student, alumni or guest!

Name: Panther Gaming
Description: Panther Gaming is a social club centered around video games. Our goal is bring together the gamers of FIU make a community unlike anything at FIU.

Name: Panther Hall
Description:
-Refrigerator
-Community kitchens on 2nd, 3rd and 4th Floor
-Laundry room on 1st Floor
-Twin extra long mattress (size 36 x 80 x 6)
-Shared bathroom

Name: Panther Moot Court
Description: This organization will provide students with the opportunity to learn case law, oral argument, and legal briefing skills. This organization will also further develop the pre-law community at FIU by providing access to an opportunity that bestows a competitive advantage on future law school applicants.

Name: Panther Power
Description: Panther Power is the spirit and pride organization that works directly with Athletics to get students excited about FIU and its athletic teams. Our goal is promote FIU pride, create a community within the student body and get student support at home games. We host pep rallies throughout the year, and many other exciting events. If you need a boost of blue and gold pride, we're the group for you!!!!! You can't fight the power, 'cause it's Panther Power!!!!!

Name: Panther Robotics
Description: Panther robotics is a student organization aimed to provide members a chance to test their skills in robotics by promoting collaborative projects and robotic competitions. We encourage students from all majors to contribute to the different stages of building a robot such as brainstorming, designing, building, programming, prototyping, testing, and upgrading the robot. Panther Robotics also aims to give back to the community by performing outreach programs based on STEM principles.

Name: Panther Roundnet
Description:
Looking for some awesome roundnet players to participate in tournaments and bring home some trophies!

 

We meet at the north turf field on Monday and Thursday from 6-9pm.

Name: Panther2Panther Mentor Collective
Description: Panther2Panther Mentor Collective enhances the student experience by linking them one-on-one with a student mentor. Students are paired with someone invested in their success — a person ready to listen, inspire, help navigate challenges, and recognize opportunities. Students will learn what to expect in school, how to approach challenges and gain career advice. At the same time, mentors will build their networks and develop skills to become better professionals and leaders.

Name: Panthers Care
Description:
Panthers Care includes:

  • Outreach aimed at educating members of the FIU community about how to identify a student in need of support
  • Workshops for student groups aimed at encouraging care and support for each other and speaking up on behalf of those in need
  • An easy way for anyone in our FIU community to anonymously share a concern about another student through an online reporting system
  • Outreach to students who self-identify or are identified by others, by providing appropriate referrals and resources to address their concerns
  • A network of campus resources that are available to assist and support students
  • An online database that students can use to easily navigate university resources

Panthers Care is not a student organization.

Name: Panthers Connect Challenge
Description:
The Panthers Connect Challenge is an engagement initiative for undergraduate students that helps you connect with your fellow Panthers. It provides you with a curated pathway to make the most of your college experience while building affinity to FIU and having fun. 

 

Want to get engaged and win great prizes? Join the Panthers Connect Challenge! Attend events, accumulate coins, and exchange them for incredible experiences and gifts.

 

https://youtu.be/5ljQEieFfX0

 

Here’s how the challenge works:

  1. Click here to go to your Paths or scroll down the Home page until you see “Paths” on the right-hand side. One of your Paths will be the “Panthers Connect Challenge 2020”. 
  2. Click on the “Panthers Connect Challenge” Path to see all the events you can attend.
  3. Events are divided into six categories:
    • Athletics & Wellness
    • Career & Professional Development
    • Research & Scholarship
    • Service & Leadership
    • Social & Interest Groups
    • World & Culture
  4. Attend two events in that category to complete it and get a virtual coin. You can get a maximum of 6 coins by completing all categories.
  5. Your coins can be used to enter exciting prize raffles throughout the year. One coin = one raffle entry. Make sure to join this organization page to stay up to date with raffle/prize announcements.
  6. When you enter a raffle, you can choose to use as many coins as you have or save them for later. Once you use one of your coins you can’t get it back!
  7. If you obtain all six coins and use them up in raffles, you can re-start the challenge by attending more events.
    • Note: you must complete all categories and use up all your coins before you are able to accumulate new coins.

Have any questions or don't see the Panthers Connect Challenge 2020 path? Email us at cse@fiu.edu for more information!

Name: Panthers Run Club
Description: Welcome to Panthers Run Club! We are more than a running club; we are a vibrant community open to individuals of all experiences and backgrounds here at FIU. Our mission is to cultivate healthy habits through running, encompassing fitness, wellness, and happiness. Join us for our weekly meetups every Monday, Wednesday, and Thursday, and be part of our community service activities, fostering a stronger sense of community within Miami!

Name: Parkview Hall
Description:
Parkview Hall is a community featuring fully furnished 4-bedroom/2-bathroom apartments. It is home to 224 upper-class students and 5 resident assistants.

Features

  • Full kitchen
  • Living room
  • Laundry room on 2nd floor
  • Full mattress (size 54 x 80 x 6)
  • Shared bathrooms

Name: Parkview Honors College EdgeLab
Description:
Now also at Parkview!

We are an organization, that focuses on giving all students the opportunity to learn, design, and make creative materials. These materials could be for cool projects, useful gadgets, or anything that you want to bring to life. We will be focusing on both the proposal, business, and design processes, as well as the actual construction and manufacturing for each project or item.

 

There will be organized educational sessions and workshops to give members the skills in preparation for making their designs and proposing their production in the future. These seminars include learning how to use a 3D printer, how to use 3D modeling software such as SolidWorks and Google SketchUp, programming business, and how to design in general.

 

We accept any FIU student from any major and any background that wants to make great things or learn how to get on the right track to making it, though Honors students will receive special offers. Don’t be afraid to contact us for more information!

Name: Phi Alpha

Name: Phi Alpha Delta Pre-Law Fraternity, International
Description: The organization prides itself to plan the best events for its members such as speakers from law school admissions, lawyers, judges, and alumni to help our members and give them the best possible resources for success. We are also very focused in the Law School Entrance Exam as well as the application process to law school. We offer workshops and discounts to LSAT course in order to benefit our members.  Our mission is as follows: Phi Alpha Delta is the world’s preeminent pre-law fraternity because of our dedication to service: Service to the student, the school, the profession, and the community. It is through devotion to the ideals of Integrity, Compassion, Courage, Professionalism, Service, Diversity, and Innovation that we better both our profession and our community. Through accepting our differences, we become not just a law fraternity, but a family.

Name: Phi Beta Sigma
Description:
We proudly represent the Lambda Tau chapter of Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, Inc., and we have been an integral part of the FIU (Florida International University) community since our charter on May 17th, 1980. As the FIRST Greek Letter organization on the FIU campus, we hold a distinguished position with a long history of active community engagement and notable achievements.

Over the years, our chapter has consistently made substantial contributions to the community, earning numerous awards that stand as a testament to our unwavering dedication. In the present year, we are particularly honored to have received the prestigious Service Impact Award at FIU, underscoring our ongoing commitment to service and the betterment of the community. Additionally, we take pride in maintaining the highest GPA within the NPHC (National Pan-Hellenic Council), demonstrating our dedication to academic excellence.

Our organization remains resolute in its mission to uplift and enhance both the FIU community and its surrounding areas. Through our continued efforts and active involvement, we are dedicated to making a lasting, positive impact.

Name: Phi Delta Phi
Description:
Phi Delta Phi©® is the oldest legal organization in continuous existence in the United States, predating even the American Bar Association. It was founded in 1869 at the University of Michigan School of Law by four law students, who at the urging of their faculty, endeavored to create an association that would foster scholarship, civility, and ethical conduct in our profession. Since that time, Phi Delta Phi©® has grown beyond the borders of the United States to Canada, Latin America and Europe.
 
Phi Delta Phi©® celebrates academic excellence and embraces the finest attributes of professionalism and scholarship. Since our founding, Phi Delta Phi©® has emphasized to students and lawyers alike the importance of our calling. Our active membership is drawn from those students of the law who not only have shown themselves companionable, but have manifested ability and industry in legal study. Similar to membership in Phi Beta Kappa in the undergraduate colleges and universities, membership in Phi Delta Phi©® is a mark of honor and distinction that follows one throughout life.
 
Academic achievement alone is not sufficient to give rise to an invitation to join Phi Delta Phi©®. Integrity, service, and excellence in all facets of human experience are considered factors for membership. In the words of our Phi Delta Phi©® forefathers, we intend that those so selected shall lead the legal profession. Once accepted, a member of Phi Delta Phi will be recognized as one whose moral compass, academic ability, and personal integrity is beyond reproach. In other words, membership is a mark of distinction.

Name: Phi Delta Theta
Description: The pinnacle fraternal and professional society, centered around the potential of each brother, the unquenchable thirst for personal development and the lifelong values of friendship, sound learning and moral rectitude.

Name: Phi Gamma Delta
Description:
Phi Gamma Delta was founded May 1, 1848, at Jefferson College in Canonsburg, Pennsylvania by the "Immortal Six" - John Templeton McCarty, Samuel Beatty Wilson, James Elliott Jr., Ellis Bailey Gregg, Daniel Webster Crofts and Naaman Fletcher.

 

 Friendship  |   Knowledge  |   Service  |   Morality  |   Excellence

 

Our Mission: Phi Gamma Delta unites men in enduring friendships, stimulates the pursuit of knowledge, and builds courageous leaders who serve the world with the best that is in them.

 

Our Vision: To be an active, vital force of men who courageously live our values and make a positive impact on college and community.

 

Follow us on Instagram, via @fiu.fiji for more information regarding recruitment interest. We will post our schedule and other content there, so don't miss it!

Name: Phi Sigma Sigma
Description: Sharing values, lifelong friendships and belonging to a sisterhood truly defines the Phi Sigma Sigma experience. Our six virtues — Friendship, Faith, Love, Sincerity, Integrity, and Strength — distinguish Phi Sigma Sigma, unite us in our activities and become ingrained in the character of our aspiring women. We embrace these values when we recruit new members, as we help our women chart the course of their college experience and, as they make decisions about career, family and community involvement.

Name: Phoenician Investment Fund
Description:
The Phoenician Investment Fund is the first Florida International University student-run finance organization with a simple purpose: Educate our members in the language of finance. Today, we pride ourselves in having prepared more than a 150 members for their dream career on Wall Street.

As a member of the Phoenician Investment Fund, you will be exposed to the nooks and crannies of multiple financial industries, including sales and trading, asset management, investment banking, corporate finance, and equity research.

Our members actively engage in activities and programs geared toward equipping them with the soft and technical skills necessary to become a well-rounded professional, thus heightening their chances of breaking into the industry of their choosing.

These simulation-based activities range from weekly business academic lectures, sponsored national competitions, mentor-ship programs, stock pitches, resume and cover letter preparation, research reports, pitch book building, industry talks, workshops, financial coding, deal talks, networking and more.
